public class JavaUtilLoggingLogger
extends AbstractLogger

An AbstractLogger that adapts the Java logging mechanism to the Liquibase logging contracts.

Field Detail

levels

public static final Map<LogLevel,Level> levels
An immutable Map of Liquibase LogLevel instances to Level instances. This field is never null and is threadsafe.

setLogLevel

public void setLogLevel(String logLevel,
                        String fileName)
Emulates the behavior of Liquibase's DefaultLogger.setLogLevel(String, String) method by simply ignoring the second argument. This method calls AbstractLogger.setLogLevel(String).

Parameters:
logLevel - the new log level; may be null
fileName - ignored; the superclass does not document what this parameter is to be used for or what its permissible values are

getLogLevel

public LogLevel getLogLevel()
Returns the LogLevel that was previously set on this JavaUtilLoggingLogger.

This implementation actually reverse engineers the LogLevel by inspecting the Logger.getLevel() of the underlying Java Logger, and using the levels Map to locate the proper LogLevel. This allows subclasses or future versions of this class to safely expose the underlying Logger if deemed necessary.

This method may return null.

Specified by:
getLogLevel in interface Logger
Overrides:
getLogLevel in class AbstractLogger
Returns:
the LogLevel used by this JavaUtilLoggingLogger instance, or null
